The FA Cup semi-finals draw will be conducted later today. A total of three clubs have booked their place in the last-4 so far. The clubs are Chelsea, Southampton and Manchester City. However, the winner between Leicester City and Manchester United will join Chelsea, Southampton and Man City in the FA Cup semi-final draw. The FA Cup semi-final draw will be held at roughly around 5:45 pm at half-time of the last quarter-final tie between Man United and Leicester City. Recall that Southampton defeated Bournemouth 3-0 on Saturday, while Man City defeated Everton 2-0. Chelsea won 2-0 against Sheffield United on Sunday.